# VoteFight Accessibility Standards

## WCAG 2.1 Compliance
- Ensure proper color contrast ratios
- Implement keyboard navigation
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide alternative text for images
- Implement screen reader support
- Use proper heading hierarchy

## Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Use proper tab order
- Implement focus indicators
- Use skip links for navigation
- Support keyboard shortcuts
- Implement proper focus management

## Screen Reader Support
- Use proper ARIA labels
- Implement semantic HTML
- Provide descriptive text
- Use proper form labels
- Implement live regions for updates
- Use proper heading structure

## Visual Accessibility
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
- Don't rely on color alone for information
- Use clear typography
- Implement high contrast mode
- Support zoom up to 200%
- Use proper spacing and sizing

## Motor Accessibility
- Use large click targets (44px minimum)
- Implement proper spacing
- Support touch navigation
- Use proper gesture support
- Implement voice control support
- Support assistive technologies

## Cognitive Accessibility
- Use clear and simple language
- Implement consistent navigation
- Provide clear error messages
- Use proper loading states
- Implement proper feedback
- Support multiple input methods